scenes.label: *start
texts: Pollon Takaoka, I assume? We're the police.
We were this close to getting outta here, and now we'd bumbled our asses right into the cops.
I'd gotten sloppy, thinking they'd all left.
You can't tell from how we look?
We're police officers as well as idols.
That explained why they looked like that. Though part of me still wondered whether they were middle-aged men in disguise.
Were they some third-rate idols doing some desperate collaboration with the police?
Looks like it's time to introduce ourselves, girls. Riko, Iroha, here we go!

scenes.label: *self_introduction
texts: I romp through the digital woods, splashing water on every hacking blaze I see! My sweeeet honeypot is gonna trap all the baddies!
I'm your cheery, frisky fawn, Bambi Kurashina☆

scenes.label: *storehis2
texts: How'd you like some meds and shots? Viruses, data tampering—nothing goes under my radar. You're not leaving 'til you change your ways.
I'm the cool-headed girl that all hackers fear: Riko Sawai.

scenes.label: *storehis3
texts: Are you bad-mouthing someone? That's a no-no♪\nSelling or buying illegal stuff? Uh uh♪\nSharing naughty pics and vids? Absolutely not♪
Be good and you'll get a reward from me♪ I'm your warm, gentle big sis, Iroha Kyogoku.

scenes.label: *storehis4
texts: We're TMPD Cyber Security Division's Cyber Countermeasures Officers!

scenes.label: *storehis5
texts: We're actual police officers! It's a pleasure to meet you!
I'm not seeing much of a reaction here.
H-how are we supposed to react...?
Hehe! You can become our fan anytime you want, young man. ♪
S-stop poking me! I ain't falling for that kinda stuff!
Bambi, stop playing around and do your job.
Geez. But this is part of our job too.
Umm, sorry if this seems sudden, but Pollon Takaoka, you are under arrest!
The weird words and poses had left me dazed, but this was no time to be spacing out!
Um, Bambi? I think you mean, "taking into custody."
Oh! Right! Please come with us.
Not happenin'. If you wanna take me, you gotta show me a warrant.
Cracking power supply system, overriding AND ignoring traffic lights... Oh, I can definitely have an arrest warrant issued, if you'd like.
You don't seem to have a profile. What's your name? Where do you live?
Did he force you to wear that strange outfit?
Did they think I was some kind of pervert?!
Well, whatever, it didn't matter right now.
She still had a sullen look on her face, and she wasn't saying a word. She couldn't even discuss her situation with the police.
That left me with one choice!
I'm "an anon with a bright future, who can't sit idly by when someone's in need!"
Without a moment to lose, I took her hand...
...and booked it away from the officers as fast as we could.
We ran through the labyrinthine passageways and old subways, deliberately taking random paths to throw them off.
Shortly after we lost them, we jumped into a worker prefab that happened to be nearby.
Momo was fresh out of breath after all that running. It didn't look like she could take another step.
Those three probably hadn't given up though. It was only a matter of time before they found us again, so we had to find a way to lose them.
No hidden room, no secret passageway...
It was a really simple prefab, where workers could change clothes or take a breather.
Some chairs were set up around a table in the middle, and we found uniforms in the lockers lining the walls.
Maybe use these as disguises... Would that work?
There was also the option of bribing the workers to sneak us out among them.
The only problem was that there wasn't a single worker here.
Would the workers show up before the cops found us? And would they be open to bribery?
Betting on that seemed hella risky.
Cross, did you hear me talk with those three?
Weren't there apps that use AR to change your looks? Would one of those work?
I mean, they exist, sure, but the good ones aren't cheap.
They're Cyber Countermeasures Officers, right? I'm pretty sure they'd see right through those.
We definitely didn't have the funds for a good one.
Whoa! They found us?! How?! I was pretty sure they didn't see us coming in here!
Then again, it's not like there was anywhere else to go.
Hey, can we talk this out?!
Sure, I hacked the traffic lights and the power supply system! I went past red lights! I was speeding, too!
But I had my reasons! You know the army went apeshit earlier, right? They were chasing us!
They're the ones that should be arrested!
Yeah, yeah, we'll hear you out. Just open up!
She didn't believe me? Were they working with the army? Or did she just think I was joking or talkin' outta my ass?
Whichever it was, it didn't seem like they were gonna listen.
I'm terribly sorry...for getting you involved in this.
Momo bowed her head in apology.
C'mon, it's not over until it's over. I haven't given up yet.
Then again, there wasn't much I could do.
Where could we go from here...?

scenes.label: *load
texts: You're not gonna stop here. This is nothing!
It can't be just me, though; Momo needs to get away also...

scenes.label: *dummy1
texts: That's right... I forgot about this.
Yeah, I guess the time is now.
It could be a trap, but...

scenes.label: *chk
texts: The next moment, I was in front of a fire, with Momo sitting right next to it.
The prefab I was just in had vanished, and when I looked up, I saw a shaft leading up to the open night sky.
As Momo tilted her head, I pointed at her stomach.
Momo got flustered and covered her stomach.
I Loaded the Save...and it worked.
I went ahead and explained what had just happened.
And now I'm back. That's why I knew what was gonna happen.
But the thing is, the Load screen popped up even though I wasn't thinking about it at all.
Someone must've done it to remind me.
It could only be one person.
The high 'n mighty super hacker that messed with my BMI and left without a trace...
...is the one who pulled me out of that shit.
And damn, I didn't like it.
...There was still no evidence of unauthorized access.
But I was pretty sure they were watching me.
They couldn't have displayed the Load screen with such perfect timing if they weren't watching me.
Maybe I should call out to them?

scenes.label: *load2
texts: If you are, why don'tcha get that Load screen up like before?
Prove to me that you exist.
Sure, you saved my ass back there, but that doesn't mean shit.
I don't trust hackers...and that includes you.
Sure, I was a hacker myself, but not outta choice.
I'm still pissed that you tampered with my BMI like it was no big deal.
Listen up. Stop acting like you're in charge here. I'm the one who's gonna decide when to Load.

scenes.label: *select2
texts: Now I definitely know that you're watchin' me.

scenes.label: *merge
texts: I don't know what you're planning...
...but with the situation being what it is, I can't be making any compromises, so I'm gonna be using this Saving and Loading thing.

scenes.label: *polonsave3
texts: With that settled, it was time to figure out our options.
The Save thumbnails were images of what I could see at the time.
I could also delete them if I wanted to.

scenes.label: *polonsave4
texts: So...what would happen if I went back and Loaded an older Save after making new data?
